example_quotes: Medical Student: So you have some muscle aches, little bit of fever, stuffy nose, sore throat, do you have any difficulty swallowing?
Patient: Uh no, it just hurts.
Medical Student: OK, do you have any neck stiffness?
Patient: No.
Medical Student: Any changes to your bowel movements recently?
Patient: Uh no, no.
Medical Student: You've had a cough at all?
Patient: No cough.
Medical Student: It doesn't feel like anything is going down the wrong way or have any coughing after you swallow?
Patient: No.
Medical Student: Any trouble breathing?
Patient: No.
Patient: Hi, um so I've had this terrible fever for the past three days...
Medical Student: The other question I suppose I should ask is, have you gotten your flu shot this year?
Patient: No, I haven't.
Medical Student: Any headaches?
Patient: Um no, no headaches.
Medical Student: OK, and have you been able to eat and drink during this time period?
Patient: Yes.
Medical Student: have you been feeling any other symptoms aside from the fever?
Patient: No.
Medical Student: Any pain anywhere else in your body?
Patient: Oh, actually um not in my joints, but I've just, there there has been some muscle ache.
Patient: Hi, um so I've had this terrible fever for the past three days um and just before that I had a stuffy nose...
Medical Student: have you had any nausea, any vomiting at all in the last little while?
Patient: No.
Medical Student: Any pain anywhere else in your body?
Patient: Uh, no.
Medical Student: And just in terms of coming back to this sore throat, do you feel like you have any swelling around your neck? Does it feel inflamed or swollen?
Patient: No.
Patient: Hi, um so I've had this terrible fever for the past three days um and just before that I had a stuffy nose...
Patient: ...and I had a sore throat, well I still do.
Medical Student: And just in terms of coming back to this sore throat, do you feel like you have any swelling around your neck? Does it feel inflamed or swollen?
Patient: No.
Medical Student: Any trouble breathing?
Patient: No.

Patient: No.
